			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I seriously hope Blacksnow wins this case. I've thought of selling my characters account in the past but knew of the &quot;infringement&quot; issues that could srise from it.<BR>
<BR>
Looking from strictly a software perspective thier is NO reason why you couldnt pass along a program IF it remains solely on the owners computer (hence the reason for purchasing numerous &quot;licenses&quot; in the case of Microsoft products). When you buy software the sale of it is strictly based on the fact that it will only find its way onto ONE computer.<BR>
<BR>
Can you move it from computer A to computer B? Sure, IF you erase it from computer A (or purchase multiple user licenses).<BR>
<BR>
EQ is no different. Verant can not stop you from handing your account over to someone else along with the discs and packaging assuming it, again, remains the property of that sole user. That's the law.<BR>
<BR>
An issue arrises though when you SELL that &quot;software&quot; for &quot;profit&quot;. I dont think anyone who is selling thier accounts is out to make a profit or somehow undermine Verant or any of these companies. All they want is the money spent during the course of thier playing time to be returned. I really do not see a problem in that.<BR>
<BR>
Is it illegal? Honestly, I dont think a law exists that could tell you whether it is or not....but this case WILL decide it for us.<BR>
<BR>
Nothing can stop me from handing over my account and software to someone else as long as I get rid of it on my machine. Can I charge, say, $50 bucks for the software? Well, thats getting iffey. Can I charge $300 for the software and the TIME spent playing the game? The answer to that is out of everyones reach at the moment but my answer would have to be......&quot;yes&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
I think the reason companies get upset about this is not the fact you are passing your account along to someone else (hell, the other option for them is for you to cancel your account entirely...by passing it on they at least still get $10 a month from SOMEone). What pisses them off is the fact this person taking your account didnt have to go out and spend the $10, $20, $30+ bucks for the software and expansions. THATS where they miss out on the money and THATS what makes em mad, heheh.
				</font>
			</td>

